# SPU-13 Geodesic Fractal Constraints (Lattice iCE40)
# v3.1 "Laminar Growth"

# --- 1. Resonant Clock (61.44 kHz) ---
# Constrained to the geometric center of the die
set_io clk_resonant 35  # iCEBreaker Example

# --- 2. Macro Placement Regions ---
# These regions define the recursive hexagonal clusters.
# We override the Manhattan router by confining Quadray logic to 60-degree wedges.

# Level 0: Core A (Invariant Axis)
# region core_a {0,0,10,10}

# Level 1: Fractal Interconnects (60-degree offsets)
# region core_b {15,0,25,10}
# region core_c {7,12,17,22}
# region core_d {22,12,32,22}

# --- 3. High-Priority Geodesic Nets ---
# Signals between lanes must maintain bit-exact phase.
# We use 'set_location' to force the Thomson Rotor bypass into zero-gate swaps.
# set_location u_rotor/bypass_p5_inst 10 10 0
